        {
            "id": "https://cazzola.click/telos.html",
            "url": "https://cazzola.click/telos.html",
            "title": "Telos",
            "summary": "<h5><strong>Details:</strong></h5>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A 3D platforming game.</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">8-week development (20h/week) with a team of 5 programmers, 4 level designers and 5 artists. Game project 4 at The Game Assembly.</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Made in TGE, the school's in-house C++ game engine.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<h5><strong>My contributions:</strong></h5>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The collision system is based on segment vs box interaction.</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The intro and outro scripted events.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"post__iframe\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/WDW5AWl-FtY?start=9&amp;mute=1\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\" data-mce-fragment=\"1\"></iframe></div>\n",
            "content_html": "<h5><strong>Details:</strong></h5>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A 3D platforming game.</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">8-week development (20h/week) with a team of 5 programmers, 4 level designers and 5 artists. Game project 4 at The Game Assembly.</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Made in TGE, the school's in-house C++ game engine.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<h5><strong>My contributions:</strong></h5>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The collision system is based on segment vs box interaction.</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The intro and outro scripted events.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"post__iframe\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/WDW5AWl-FtY?start=9&amp;mute=1\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\" data-mce-fragment=\"1\"></iframe></div>\n\n<h5>Segment vs box collision system:</h5>\n<figure class=\"post__image\"><img loading=\"lazy\"  style=\"outline: 3px solid rgba(var(--color-primary-rgb), 0.55)  !important;\" src=\"https://cazzola.click/media/posts/2/telos-collision.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"440\" height=\"248\"></figure>\n<p>During the project I implemented the collision system which was based on <a href=\"https://youtu.be/8JJ-4JgR7Dg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">javidx9 Youtube video</a>. <span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The system works by that dynamic object creates a segment from its current position to the next position in the direction of its velocity. If the segment hits a box it will move the dynamic object to the hit point. If the segment does not hit a box it will move the dynamic object to the end of the segment. This solution is frame independent so the dynamic object will still collide with boxes during very low framerates.</span></p>\n<figure class=\"post__image\"><img loading=\"lazy\"  src=\"https://cazzola.click/media/posts/2/ray_vs_box.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"653\" height=\"368\"></figure>",
            "image": "https://cazzola.click/media/posts/2/telos_medium.gif",
            "author": {
                "name": "Marcus Cazzola"
            },
            "tags": [
                   "Group Projects"
            ],
            "date_published": "2023-02-04T12:34:52+01:00",
            "date_modified": "2023-03-21T10:54:02+01:00"
        },
        {
            "id": "https://cazzola.click/hamer-time.html",
            "url": "https://cazzola.click/hamer-time.html",
            "title": "Hammer Time",
            "summary": "<h5>Details:</h5>\n<h6></h6>\n<h6></h6>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A 2D game inspired by Ikaruga.</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">8-week development (20h/week) with a team of 5 programmers, 3 level designers and 4 artists. Game project 3 at The Game Assembly.</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Made in TGA2D, the school's in-house C++ game engine.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<h5><strong>My contributions:</strong></h5>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Player movement.</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Xbox and keyboard input manager.</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sprite sheet-based animations.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"post__iframe\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/AQroTOqMwWY?start=15&amp;mute=1\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></div>\n",
            "content_html": "<h5>Details:</h5>\n<h6></h6>\n<h6></h6>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A 2D game inspired by Ikaruga.</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">8-week development (20h/week) with a team of 5 programmers, 3 level designers and 4 artists. Game project 3 at The Game Assembly.</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Made in TGA2D, the school's in-house C++ game engine.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<h5><strong>My contributions:</strong></h5>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Player movement.</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Xbox and keyboard input manager.</span></li>\n<li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sprite sheet-based animations.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"post__iframe\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/AQroTOqMwWY?start=15&amp;mute=1\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></div>\n\n<h5>Sprite sheet<strong>-based animations:</strong></h5>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">I had to develop a pipeline for importing sprite sheets into the TGA2D game engine during the project. I came up with a solution where the artist used</span><a href=\"https://www.codeandweb.com/texturepacker\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">TexturePacker</span></a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> </span><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">to export the sprite sheet image and a JSON file that described the coordinates of each sprite. I also developed an animation system capable of switching between different animations.</span></p>\n<figure class=\"post__image\"><img loading=\"lazy\"  src=\"https://cazzola.click/media/posts/1/sheet_game_crop.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"4081\" height=\"1351\" sizes=\"(min-width: 37.5em) 1600px, 80vw\" srcset=\"https://cazzola.click/media/posts/1/responsive/sheet_game_crop-xs.png 384w ,https://cazzola.click/media/posts/1/responsive/sheet_game_crop-sm.png 600w ,https://cazzola.click/media/posts/1/responsive/sheet_game_crop-md.png 768w ,https://cazzola.click/media/posts/1/responsive/sheet_game_crop-lg.png 1200w ,https://cazzola.click/media/posts/1/responsive/sheet_game_crop-xl.png 1600w\"></figure><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Here is an example of how to sprite sheet JSON file was structured:</span></p>\n<pre>{\"frames\": {<br>\"enemy_beam_blue.png\":<br>{<br>    \"frame\": {\"x\":3882,\"y\":414,\"w\":176,\"h\":117},<br>    \"rotated\": false,<br>    \"trimmed\": false,<br>    \"spriteSourceSize\": {\"x\":0,\"y\":0,\"w\":176,\"h\":117},<br>    \"sourceSize\": {\"w\":176,\"h\":117}<br>},<br>\"enemy_beam_blue1.png\":<br>{<br>    \"frame\": {\"x\":2,\"y\":533,\"w\":176,\"h\":117},<br>    \"rotated\": false,<br>    \"trimmed\": false,<br>    \"spriteSourceSize\": {\"x\":0,\"y\":0,\"w\":176,\"h\":117},<br>    \"sourceSize\": {\"w\":176,\"h\":117}<br>},</pre>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The biggest challenge I had was the transitions between the different animations. Some animations like the player flip were not supposed to be cancelled mid animation, so the team has to put \"overrideable\": false in the animation JSON file. This resulted in me having to keep track of the new animation request and only switch to a new animation at the last frame of the previous animation.</span></p>\n<figure class=\"post__image\"><img loading=\"lazy\"  src=\"https://cazzola.click/media/posts/1/sp3_player_flip-2.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"118\" height=\"110\"></figure>\n<pre>...<br>\"flip_blue_to_orange\":<br>        {<br>            \"frames\":<br>            [<br>                \"player_blueToOrange1.png\",<br>                \"player_blueToOrange2.png\",<br>                \"player_blueToOrange3.png\",<br>                \"player_blueToOrange4.png\",<br>                \"player_blueToOrange5.png\",<br>                \"player_blueToOrange6.png\",<br>                \"player_blueToOrange7.png\"<br>            ],<br>            \"frames per second\": 30,<br>            \"overrideable\": false<br>        },<br>...</pre>",
            "image": "https://cazzola.click/media/posts/1/sp3.gif",
            "author": {
                "name": "Marcus Cazzola"
            },
